{
  "text": "We previously found that depletion of hspB1 in HeLa cells inhibits the activation by IL-1 or TNF of pro-inflammatory signalling and induction of inflammatory response genes [CITATION_1] . Inhibition of upstream signalling in HeLa cells [CITATION_2] and inflammatory gene expression in human umbilical vein endothelial cells [CITATION_3] and in an angiogenic breast cancer cell line [CITATION_4] has been confirmed by others. However, depletion of the small heat shock protein by different siRNAs was found to increase TNF-induced nuclear factor-kB activation in HeLa [CITATION_5] and TNF-induced prostaglandin E 2 production and IL-8 expression in human keratinocytes [CITATION_6] . The possibility of siRNA-associated off-target and cell type-dependent effects renders the function of hspB1 in inflammatory gene expression unclear and emphasises the need for a complete gene knockout.",
  "correct_citation": {
